Programme of Events
2.45-3 p.m.:
Guests assemble in special area
on tarmac adjacent to Overseas Terminal.
3.10 p.m.:
Senator the Hon. Shane Paltridge, Minister for
Civil Aviation, and Mrs. Paltridge arrive and are
welcomed by Sir Hudson Fysh, K.B.E., D.F.C.,
Chairman, Qantas Empire Airways, and Lady
Fysh.
3.18 р.m.:
Captain G. U. Allan, C.B.E., A.F.C., Deputy
Chief Executive and Deputy General Manager,
Qantas Empire Airways, welcomes guests and
introduces Sir Hudson Fysh.
3.28 p.m.:
Sir Hudson invites Mrs. Paltridge to christen the
flagship of the Qantas 707 Jetliner fleet, the
"City of Canberra".
3.33p.m.: Sir Hudson requests the passengers travelling on
the inaugural flight and the first scheduled jet
service in Australian commercial aviation history
to board the "City of Canberra".
3.35 p.m.: Senator Paltridge is invited by Sir Hudson to
officially open the Qantas jet service from Aus-
tralia to the U.S.A.
3.45 p.m.: The Hon. C. W.
Davidson, O.B.E., M.P.,
Postmaster-General, officially hands over to the
Commander of the "City of Canberra" the first
airmail to be carried by jet across the Pacific.
4 p.m.:
Mrs. Paltridge cuts the ribbon and
the "City of Canberra"
moves on to the runway
for take-off.
Refreshments served in the 1st floor lounge of
the Overseas Terminal.
AUSTRALIA'S
QANTAS
ROUND -THE - WORLD AIRLINE
